==English==

===Pronunciation===
*(''verb''): ĭnvīt', /ɪnˈvaɪt/, /<tt>In"vaIt</tt>/
*(''noun''): ĭn'vīt, /ˈɪnvaɪt/, /<tt>"InvaIt</tt>/
[[Category:English heteronyms]]

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|invit|e}}
[[Category:English transitive verbs]]

#To [[ask for]] the [[presence]] or [[participation]] of someone.
#:''We '''invited''' our friends round for dinner.''
#To [[request]] [[formally]].
#:''I '''invite''' you all to be seated.''
#To [[encourage]].
#:''I always '''invite''' criticism of my definitions.''
#:''Wearing that skimpy dress, you are bound to '''invite''' attention.''

====Synonyms====
*(''ask for the presence or participation of''): [[ask out]]
*(''request formally''): [[ask]], [[beseech]], [[entreat]], [[request]]
*(''encourage''): [[ask for]], [[encourage]], [[provoke]]

